# How to create a Record in a JS migration · pocketbase pocketbase · Discussion #1464
created: 2023-01-02, last updated: 2026-04-16, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/1464)

Currently the JS migrations are not documented well (*I'm planning to update the documentation together with the upcoming JS hooks support in v0.13/v0.14 since it will require restructuring the sections anyway*) but if you want to create a collection or record programmatically you can refer to the Go APIs:
- https://pocketbase.io/docs/collection-methods/
- https://pocketbase.io/docs/record-methods/
...
So for example, to create a Record programmatically in a migration you can do something like the following:
```
// ./pocketbase migrate create 'add_new_record'
migrate((db) => { // up
const dao = new Dao(db)
const collection = dao.findCollectionByNameOrId("example")
const record = new Record(collection, {
"title": "example",
})
dao.saveRecord(record);
}, (db) => { // down
const dao = new Dao(db)
// delete the previously created record (if exists)
try {
const record = dao.findFirstRecordByData("example", "title", "example")
dao.deleteRecord(record);
} catch {}
})
```
...
All the changes are stored automatically as migrations files.

