# Case Insensitive Usernames #6337 - GitHub
created: 2025-01-23, last updated: 2026-04-17, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/6337)

For now if you don't want to update your db, a workaround could be to attach to the `OnRecordAuthWithPasswordRequest` hook and set `e.Record` on your own.
...
If you know what you're doing you can open the data.db with an sqlite client and run this:
`UPDATE users SET username=lower(username);`
(maybe rename the users table if you're using another auth collection)
...
- JS `pb_hooks`:
```
onRecordAuthWithPasswordRequest((e) => {
try {
if (!e.record) {
// try to lookup for the username field in caseinsensitive manner
// or any other more advanced checks like e.app.recordQuery("users").andWhere($dbx.exp("username = {:username} COLLATE NOCASE", {"username": e.identity}).limit(1).one(e.record)
e.record = e.app.findFirstRecordByFilter("users", "username:lower={:username}", {
"username": e.identity.toLowerCase(),
})
}
} catch {
// there is no need to throw as the record existence and its password would be further validated by the finalizer of the hook
}
return e.next()
}, "users")

